#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.80"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.80:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.80:0.2"
msgid "8. Gilānavagga "
msgstr "8. Sick "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 80. Dutiyaavijjāpahānasutta → dutiyaavijjāsuttaṃ (bj) | avijjā 2 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.80:0.3"
msgid "80. Dutiyaavijjāpahānasutta "
msgstr "80. Giving Up Ignorance (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn35.80:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu … pe … etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha … and asked him, "

msgctxt "sn35.80:1.2"
msgid "“atthi nu kho, bhante, eko dhammo yassa pahānā bhikkhuno avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjatī”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, is there one thing such that by giving it up a mendicant gives up ignorance and gives rise to knowledge?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn35.80:2.1"
msgid "“Atthi kho, bhikkhu, eko dhammo yassa pahānā bhikkhuno avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjatī”ti. "
msgstr "“There is, mendicant.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn35.80:3.1"
msgid "“Katamo pana, bhante, eko dhammo yassa pahānā bhikkhuno avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjatī”ti? "
msgstr "“But what is that one thing?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn35.80:4.1"
msgid "“Avijjā kho, bhikkhu, eko dhammo yassa pahānā bhikkhuno avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjatī”ti. "
msgstr "“Ignorance is one thing such that by giving it up a mendicant gives up ignorance and gives rise to knowledge.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn35.80:5.1"
msgid "“Kathaṃ pana, bhante, jānato, kathaṃ passato avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjatī”ti? "
msgstr "“But how does a mendicant know and see so as to give up ignorance and give rise to knowledge?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn35.80:6.1"
msgid "“Idha, bhikkhu, bhikkhuno sutaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "“It’s when a mendicant has heard: "

msgctxt "sn35.80:6.2"
msgid "‘sabbe dhammā nālaṃ abhinivesāyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Nothing is worth clinging on to.’ "

msgctxt "sn35.80:6.3"
msgid "Evañcetaṃ, bhikkhu, bhikkhuno sutaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "When a mendicant has heard that "

msgctxt "sn35.80:6.4"
msgid "‘sabbe dhammā nālaṃ abhinivesāyā’ti. "
msgstr "nothing is worth clinging on to, "

# NOTE: Surely annato here is equivalent to parato, contra BB.
msgctxt "sn35.80:6.5"
msgid "So sabbaṃ dhammaṃ abhijānāti, sabbaṃ dhammaṃ abhiññāya sabbaṃ dhammaṃ parijānāti, sabbaṃ dhammaṃ pariññāya sabbanimittāni aññato passati, cakkhuṃ aññato passati, rūpe … "
msgstr "they directly know all things. Directly knowing all things, they completely understand all things. Completely understanding all things, they see all signs as other. They see the eye, sights, "

msgctxt "sn35.80:6.6"
msgid "cakkhuviññāṇaṃ … "
msgstr "eye consciousness, "

msgctxt "sn35.80:6.7"
msgid "cakkhusamphassaṃ … "
msgstr "and eye contact as other. "

msgctxt "sn35.80:6.8"
msgid "yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi aññato passati … pe … "
msgstr "And they also see the pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact as other. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.80:6.9"
msgid "manaṃ aññato passati, dhamme … "
msgstr "They see the mind, thoughts, "

msgctxt "sn35.80:6.10"
msgid "manoviññāṇaṃ … "
msgstr "mind consciousness, "

msgctxt "sn35.80:6.11"
msgid "manosamphassaṃ … "
msgstr "and mind contact as other. "

msgctxt "sn35.80:6.12"
msgid "yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi aññato passati. "
msgstr "And they also see the pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact as other. "

msgctxt "sn35.80:6.13"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhu, jānato evaṃ passato bhikkhuno avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjatī”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant knows and sees so as to give up ignorance and give rise to knowledge.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.80:6.14"
msgid "Sattamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

